# Med Rex App Website

Professional website for Med Rex App medication management app, featuring board-certified pharmacist reviews.

## Setup Instructions

### 1. Add Hero Images

Place your 9 hero images in the `images/` folder with the following names:
- `Home1.png`
- `Home2.png`
- `Home3.png`
- `Home4.png`
- `Home5.png`
- `Home6.png`
- `Home7.png`
- `Home8.png`
- `Home9.png`

These images will automatically rotate on the homepage hero section every 4 seconds.

### 2. Optional: Add Additional Images

For best visual appearance, you can also add these optional images:
- `pharmacist-review.png` - Board-certified pharmacist reviewing medications
- `doctor-time.png` - Busy doctor with limited time
- `adherence-chart.png` - Adherence tracking charts
- `family-care.png` - Family caregiver support
- `mission.png` - Our mission image
- `pharmacist1.jpg` through `pharmacist6.jpg` - Team member photos
- `ceo.jpg`, `vpsales.jpg`, `cmo.jpg` - Leadership team photos

If these images are not provided, the website will display gradient placeholders.

### 3. File Structure

```
MedRexAppWebsite/
├── index.html          # Homepage
├── about.html          # About page
├── team.html           # Meet Our Team page
├── privacy.html        # Privacy Policy page
├── contact.html        # Contact Us page
├── css/
│   └── styles.css      # Main stylesheet
├── js/
│   └── main.js         # JavaScript functionality
├── images/             # Image assets folder
└── README.md           # This file
```

### 4. Running the Website

#### Option 1: Simple Local Server (Python)
```bash
cd /Volumes/SanDisk4TB2_WorkingDrive/Xcode/Xcode\ and\ VS\ Code\ Projects/MedRexAppWebsite
python3 -m http.server 8000
```
Then open http://localhost:8000 in your browser.

#### Option 2: VS Code Live Server
1. Install the "Live Server" extension in VS Code
2. Right-click on `index.html`
3. Select "Open with Live Server"

#### Option 3: Direct File Opening
Simply double-click `index.html` to open in your default browser.

